%S A395655 1,6,38,246,1611,10624,70386,467838,3117047,20805726,139072968,
%T A395655 930678504,6233938452,41788997928,280313728378,1881340559502,
%U A395655 12632729690943,84860617939234,570258477706182,3833320125283686,25775105024098083,173354244471699264,1166180646532192632
%N A395655 Expansion of 1/(4*x) * (1/(3-2*g)^2 - 1), where g = 1+x*g^3 is the g.f. of A001764.
%H A395655 Marko Riedel et al, <a href="https://math.stackexchange.com/questions/5084451/">Identity between two generating functions</a>
%F A395655 G.f.: g^3*(2-g)/(3-2*g)^2, where g = 1+x*g^3 is the g.f. of A001764.
%F A395655 Sum_{k>=1} a(k-1) * x^k/k = (1/6) * log( Sum_{k>=0} binomial(3*k+3,k) * x^k ).
%F A395655 a(n) = A378504(n)/(n+1) = (1/6) * (binomial(3*n+2,n) + Sum_{k=0..n+1} 2^(n+1-k) * binomial(3*n+3,k)).
%F A395655 a(n) = (1/(n+1)) * Sum_{k=0..n} 2^k * binomial(k+2,2) * binomial(3*n+3,n-k).
%o A395655 (PARI) a(n) = (binomial(3*n+2, n)+sum(k=0, n+1, 2^(n+1-k)*binomial(3*n+3, k)))/6;
%Y A395655 Cf. A001700, A395656, A395657.
%Y A395655 Cf. A395668, A395669.
%Y A395655 Cf. A001764, A004319, A378504.
%K A395655 nonn,new
